Here are 3 ways yoga changed my life:

1. Yoga transformed my relationship with myself.
After heartbreak, injury, and losing a loved one, yoga became my way home.
Each pose helped me listen inward. Each breath rebuilt my confidence and softness.

2. Yoga regulated my nervous system.
The city moves fast. Yoga slows me down.
Through breathwork and grounding postures, I learned how to calm my physiology, unclench stress, and feel safe in my body again.

3. Yoga gave me community.
I practice and teach surrounded by family, friends, and neighbors ‚Äî in studios, at parties, on rooftops, and over tea.
